data.enText: to look at every part of sth carefully, especially because you are looking for a particular thing or person

data.chText: 他仔细眺望地平线，找寻陆地的踪影。
data.enText: He scanned the horizon for any sign of land.

data.chText: 她急切地端详着他的脸。
data.enText: She scanned his face anxiously.
to look quickly but not very carefully at a document, etc.

data.chText: 我很快浏览了一下名单，看有没有我的名字。
data.enText: I scanned the list quickly for my name.

data.chText: 她边吃早饭，边浏览报纸。
data.enText: She scanned through the newspaper over breakfast.
to get an image of an object, a part of sb's body, etc. on a computer by passing X-rays , ultrasound waves or electromagnetic waves over it in a special machine

data.chText: 研究人员对他们的大脑加以扫描，以监视病情的发展。
data.enText: Their brains are scanned so that researchers can monitor the progress of the disease.
to pass across an area

data.chText: 几台暗藏的摄像机把院子里的每一个角落都拍了进去。
data.enText: Concealed video cameras scan every part of the compound.
to examine a computer program or document in order to look for a virus

data.chText: 这个软件是为搜索所有新文件的病毒而设计。
data.enText: This software is designed to scan all new files for viruses.

data.chText: （用扫描设备）扫描（图像或文件等）

data.chText: 怎样把照片扫描并放到电子邮件的附件呢？
data.enText: How do I scan a photo and attach it to an email?

to have a scan
the act of looking quickly through sth written or printed, usually in order to find sth

means: （用扫描设备）扫描（图像或文件等）

ex.chText: 他快速翻阅报纸，没有发现什么特别的新闻。
ex.enText: He scanned through the newspapers and found nothing special.

ex.chText: 她粗略地看了一下名单，想知道是否有她的名字。
ex.enText: She scanned the list of names to see if hers was on it.

synonyms.bx: 又作 scan through, 指粗略地扫视报刊文章等，以便了解主要内容，含较强的目的性。

ex.chText: 买本杂志或逛一下礼品商店。
ex.enText: Buy a magazine or browse in the gift shop.

ex.chText: 他喜欢星期天在旧书店翻阅旧书。
ex.enText: He likes to browse through old books on Sundays in old book stores.

ex.chText: 公众可以浏览市政会的网页，以获取最新信息。
ex.enText: The public can browse through the City Council's home page for the latest information.

ex.chText: 这一功能让你可以浏览硬盘驱动器。
ex.enText: This feature allows you to browse your hard drive.

synonyms.bx: 指随意浏览书刊、计算机、因特网等，目的在于寻找有趣的信息或挑选中意的物品，常后接介词 through。

ex.chText: 你可以先略读一下目录。
ex.enText: You can skim through the catalogue first.

ex.chText: 那个学生快速阅读了考卷。
ex.enText: The student skimmed through the test paper.

ex.chText: 不要逐字细读文件，大致看一下就可以了。
ex.enText: Don't read the document word for word, just skim it.

synonyms.bx: 指快速阅读以找出要点或主要信息，常后接介词 through/over。

data.enText: scan sth into sth
scan sth in
to pass light over a picture or document using a scanner in order to copy it and put it in the memory of a computer

data.chText: 文字和图画可以扫描进计算机。
data.enText: Text and pictures can be scanned into the computer.

tr: systematic examination of a prescribed region
example: he made a thorough scan of the beach with his binoculars
you could see the tumor in the CAT scan
This dictionary can be read by the computer

tr: make a wide, sweeping search of
example: The beams scanned the night sky

tr: in electronics, to reproduce an image

example: She scanned the newspaper headlines while waiting for the taxi

value.def: When you scan written material, you look through it quickly in order to find important or interesting information.

example.ex: She scanned the advertisement pages of the newspapers...
example.tran: 她浏览了一下报纸的广告页。

example.ex: I haven't read much into it as yet. I've only just scanned through it.
example.tran: 我还没有细细研读，只是粗略地翻看了一下。

example.ex: I just had a quick scan through your book again.
example.tran: 我只是又快速浏览了一遍你的书。

value.def: When you scan a place or group of people, you look at it carefully, usually because you are looking for something or someone.

example.tran: 那名警官仔细检查了房间。

example.ex: She was nervous and kept scanning the crowd for Paul...
example.tran: 她很紧张，眼睛不停地在人群中搜寻保罗。

example.ex: He raised the binoculars to his eye again, scanning across the scene.
example.tran: 他再一次把双筒望远镜举到眼前，仔细观察整个现场。

value.def: If people scan something such as luggage, they examine it using a machine that can show or find things inside it that cannot be seen from the outside.

example.ex: Their approach is to scan every checked-in bag with a bomb detector.
example.tran: 他们的方法是用炸弹探测器对每一个办理了登机手续的箱包进行扫描。

value.def: If a computer disk is scanned, a program on the computer checks the disk to make sure that it does not contain a virus.

example.ex: The disk has no viruses — I've scanned it already.
example.tran: 这个盘没有感染病毒——我已经扫描过了。

value.def: If a picture or document is scanned into a computer, a machine passes a beam of light over it to make a copy of it in the computer.

example.ex: The entire paper contents of all libraries will eventually be scanned into computers...
example.tran: 所有图书馆的全部纸质内容最终都会被扫描进电脑。

example.ex: Designs can also be scanned in from paper.
example.tran: 设计图也可以从纸上扫描进电脑。

value.def: If a radar or sonar machine scans an area, it examines or searches it by sending radar or sonar beams over it.

example.ex: The ship's radar scanned the sea ahead.
example.tran: 船上的雷达扫描了前方的海域。

value.def: A scan is a medical test in which a machine sends a beam of X-rays over a part of your body in order to check that it is healthy.

example.ex: He was rushed to hospital for a brain scan.
example.tran: 他被火速送往医院做脑部扫描。

example.ex: ...a breast scan to check for cancer.
example.tran: 为诊察癌症所做的乳腺扫描检查

value.def: If a pregnant woman has a scan, a machine using sound waves produces an image of her womb on a screen so that a doctor can see if her baby is developing normally.
If a line of a poem does not scan, it is not the right length or does not have emphasis in the right places to match the rest of the poem.

example.ex: He had written a few poems. Sid told him they didn't scan.
example.tran: 他写了几首诗。锡德告诉他那几首诗都不押韵。
